  _frames:
  - _image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 2c77fd52d865a574e983192c084f1b5a, type: 3}
    _text: "February, 10th, 1756 <br>Near S\xE3o Gabriel, more than 3,000 of Spanish
      and Portuguese soldiers fought the Guarani Battle of Caiboat\xE9.  <br>In less
      than two hours, more than a 1,500 of Guarani people were killed by the army,
      even after surrending themselves, and hundreds of others were arrested, tortured
      and killed later. The europeans suffered 4 deaths."
  - _image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: df58d9328dd861f4ba40eaee947d003f, type: 3}
    _text: 'Still in this day, the Guarani War is still considered of the the most
      brutal slaughter in Brazil, and it is a  hallmark of the bloody conquest of
      South America by Europeans. <br>The attack against Brazilian indigenous peoples
      is back in force. '
  - _image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: df58d9328dd861f4ba40eaee947d003f, type: 3}
    _text: 'Indigenous peoples are dying as Brazilian politicians deliberately allow
      farmers and soy planters to steal and destroy indigenous territories. The key
      to the survival and prosperity of indigenous peoples is ensuring that their
      land remains under their control. '
  - _image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 446217968ed2f6b448fd8f07bb7d76f6, type: 3}
    _text: 'teste dfgdfgdfg '
  - _image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 07d23ffc69744e0418147dc5b8460209, type: 3}
    _text: "\"What counts for us is our land. This is worth more than life. And we
      are the ones who can sustain nature, who never destroy or pollute our river.
      We take care of our land, we know its value. We need to protect what our ancestors
      left us.\"<br> - Manifest of Piara\xE7u, written in 2020 by representatives
      of 45 indigenous peoples in Brazil"
